{
  "doc_id": "47428",
  "text": "Replication stress is associated with the generation of single-stranded DNA (ssDNA) at the replication fork, which serves to recruit and activate the ataxia-telangiectasia and Rad3 related (ATR) kinase [CITATION_1] . The ATR kinase modulates the replication stress response by activating and recruiting DNA repair machinery, preventing new origin firing, promoting replication fork stability, and stimulating processing for replication restart [CITATION_2] . In the absence of ATR, replication stress leads to extensive ssDNA formation, which may result in replication protein A (RPA) exhaustion and DNA breakage [CITATION_3] ).",
